{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Introduce a deposit payment scheme for cigarette butts",
        "additional_details": "Cigarette butt litter accounts for around a third of all litter on our streets. \r\n\r\nThere have been many attempts to reduce the amount of litter but most are only local efforts with varying degrees of effectiveness.\r\n\r\nThe results of this initiative will be cleaner streets, with no major outlay by smokers (other than the first pack) or no change to the litter problem but a massive saving to local councils to remove this blight from our streets.",
        "background": "Make buyers pay a deposit that is refunded when all the butts are returned.\r\n\r\nThe charge is added to the cost of a box of cigarettes, as much as \u00a31, and is returned by the seller when the butts are returned, ideally in the original box.",
